---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — STR Host Tools"
  description="Privacy policy for strhost.tools. How we handle the (very limited) data the site collects."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <section class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9">
      <p class="label text-gold-deep">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-h1 font-serif text-navy leading-tight">
        Privacy Policy<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lead text-ink-2">
        A full privacy policy is in development. The short version: strhost.tools is a static calculator site with no user accounts, no databases, and no saved calculations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-parchment-light border-t border-rule">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-9 prose">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">What we collect</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Standard server logs (IP, user-agent, timestamp). If you submit the email-capture form, we store the email address you provide for the lead-magnet PDF.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Analytics & ads</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        We use Google Analytics 4 for traffic measurement and may serve Google AdSense ads on calculator pages. Both set cookies in your browser per Google's policies.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Calculator inputs</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Numbers you type into a calculator stay in the URL of your browser tab. We don't transmit them to a server. Closing the tab discards them.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-7 text-caption text-ink-3 italic">
        Last updated: this stub is a placeholder. See <a href="/terms" class="text-navy">Terms</a> and <a href="/disclosures" class="text-navy">Disclosures</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
